Class IntegerValue<T extends IntegerValue<T>>

java.lang.Object

Direct Known Subclasses:
MatrixColumnIndex, MatrixRowIndex
public abstract class IntegerValue<T extends IntegerValue<T>>
extends RBNumeric<T>
A base class for creating typesafe versions of an Integer, with two goals: tightening semantics, and making code easier to read.

This is like PreciseValue and ImpreciseValue, but for int typesafe wrappers. Like those two, it lets us have more clearly named comparison methods: val1.isLessThan(val2) is clearer than val1.compareTo(val2) < 0 More importantly, since Java doesn't allow typedefs, it gives us a general way to implement simple wrappers around a single int.
